CHANGELOG.md:214: - Fixed `/exit` and `/quit` waiting one shutdown timeout per hanging extension by running `session_shutdown` handlers within a shared shutdown window ([#2736](https://github.com/can1357/oh-my-pi/issues/2736)).
CHANGELOG.md:257: - Hook API: `before_agent_start` handlers can now return `systemPromptAppend` to dynamically append text to the system prompt for that turn. Multiple hooks' appends are concatenated.
CHANGELOG.md:258: - Hook API: `before_agent_start` handlers can now return multiple messages (all are injected, not just the first)
CHANGELOG.md:441: - Fixed Ctrl+C teardown waiting up to 30s when an extension's `session_shutdown` handler hung — observed on Windows with `omp-discord-presence` 0.1.2 stuck on a stale Discord IPC pipe. `ExtensionRunner.emit` previously shared the generic 30s `EXTENSION_HANDLER_TIMEOUT_MS` budget for every event, including the fire-and-forget teardown event extensions cannot observe. `session_shutdown` now uses a dedicated 2s `SESSION_SHUTDOWN_HANDLER_TIMEOUT_MS` cap routed through a per-event `handlerTimeoutForE... [truncated]
CHANGELOG.md:1162: - Fixed `task`-spawned subagents repeating filesystem scans the parent had already completed. `ExecutorOptions` and the `createAgentSession()` call inside `runSubprocess()` did not forward `rules`, the discovered extension paths, or the discovered `.omp/tools/` paths, so each subagent re-ran `loadCapability<Rule>()`, `discoverAndLoadExtensions()`, and the full `.omp/tools/` walk. The toolsession now caches `session.rules`, `session.extensionPaths`, and `session.customToolPaths`; `runSubprocess()... [truncated]
CHANGELOG.md:2366: - Fixed extension `ctx.ui.notify()` messages emitted during `session_start` being cleared before the first interactive render ([#1316](https://github.com/can1357/oh-my-pi/issues/1316)).
CHANGELOG.md:3109: - Changed session system-prompt APIs to use ordered string block arrays by requiring `buildSystemPrompt`, `CreateAgentSessionOptions.systemPrompt`, `Session.rebuildSystemPrompt`, and extension `before_agent_start`/`getSystemPrompt` hooks to accept and return `systemPrompt: string[]` instead of a plain system-prompt string or separate `projectPrompt` field
CHANGELOG.md:6913: - New `getCommands()` method in ExtensionAPI to retrieve available slash commands
CHANGELOG.md:8375: - Added ExtensionAPI `setLabel()` for extension and entry labels
CHANGELOG.md:8828: - `before_agent_start` event receives `systemPrompt` in the event object and returns `systemPrompt` (full replacement) instead of `systemPromptAppend`
CHANGELOG.md:9885: - `pi.setLabel(entryId, label)` in ExtensionAPI for setting per-entry labels from extensions ([#806](https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/806))
CHANGELOG.md:9918: - Extension commands can provide argument auto-completions via `getArgumentCompletions` in `pi.registerCommand()` ([#775](https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/pull/775) by [@ribelo](https://github.com/ribelo))
CHANGELOG.md:9931: - Fixed extension messages rendering twice on startup when `pi.sendMessage({ display: true })` is called during `session_start` ([#765](https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/pull/765) by [@dannote](https://github.com/dannote))
CHANGELOG.md:10195: - `before_agent_start` event now receives `systemPrompt` in the event object and returns `systemPrompt` (full replacement) instead of `systemPromptAppend`. Extensions that were appending must now use `event.systemPrompt + extra` pattern. ([#575](https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/575))
CHANGELOG.md:10204: - `setActiveTools()` in ExtensionAPI for dynamic tool management
CHANGELOG.md:10266: - ExtensionAPI: `setModel()`, `getThinkingLevel()`, `setThinkingLevel()` methods for extensions to change model and thinking level at runtime ([#509](https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/509))
CHANGELOG.md:10274: - `docs/extensions.md`: Exhaustive example links for all ExtensionAPI methods and events
CHANGELOG.md:10402: - `HookAPI` → `ExtensionAPI`
CHANGELOG.md:10406: - `CustomToolAPI` → `ExtensionAPI` (merged)
CHANGELOG.md:10425: import type { ExtensionAPI } from "@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent";
CHANGELOG.md:10426: export default function (pi: ExtensionAPI) {
CHANGELOG.md:10428:   pi.registerTool({ name: "my_tool", ... });
CHANGELOG.md:10432: **Custom tools now have full context access.** Tools registered via `pi.registerTool()` now receive the same `ctx` object that event handlers receive. Previously, custom tools had limited context. Now all extension code shares the same capabilities:
CHANGELOG.md:10434: - `pi.registerTool()` - Register tools the LLM can call
CHANGELOG.md:10435: - `pi.registerCommand()` - Register commands like `/mycommand`
CHANGELOG.md:10439: - `pi.on()` - Subscribe to lifecycle events (tool_call, session_start, etc.)
CHANGELOG.md:10603: - The monolithic `session` event is now split into granular events: `session_start`, `session_before_switch`, `session_switch`, `session_before_branch`, `session_branch`, `session_before_compact`, `session_compact`, `session_shutdown`
CHANGELOG.md:10606: - New `before_agent_start` event: inject messages before the agent loop starts
CHANGELOG.md:10614: - New `pi.registerCommand(name, options)` for custom slash commands (handler receives `HookCommandContext`)
CHANGELOG.md:10818: - **Snake game example hook**: Demonstrates `ui.custom()`, `registerCommand()`, and session persistence. See [examples/hooks/snake.ts](examples/hooks/snake.ts).

